    "name": "Bore Worm Monarch",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "html": "A single, finger-length bore worm has never been much of a threat to any one creature, but isolated bore worms are found only in laboratories. Bore worm swarms, as they are more commonly encountered, consume organic material with a voracious appetite, tunneling through the earth like water as they reach progressively larger sizes."
        }
    ],
